article.description: — Robert Vaihola and Omari Moore scored 15 points apiece and San Jose State slipped past Ball State 67-65 at the Nassau Championship on Sunday.
article.headline: Vaihola's 15 help San Jose State defeat Ball State 67-65
article.linkText: Vaihola's 15 help San Jose State defeat Ball State 67-65
article.story: NASSAU, Bahamas -- — Robert Vaihola and Omari Moore scored 15 points apiece and San Jose State slipped past Ball State 67-65 at the Nassau Championship on Sunday. Vaihola scored the game-winning basket on a layup with 2 seconds left. Vaihola had eight rebounds for the Spartans (6-2), while Moore handed out five assists. Trey Anderson shot 3 for 7 from beyond the arc to finish with 11 points. Payton Sparks paced the Cardinals (4-3) with 14 points and 10 rebounds. Demarius Jacobs added 14 points and two blocks. Jalen Windham also scored 14. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
